nvidia-384 driver + bumblebee: http://lenovolinux.blogspot.ro/2016/05/bumblebee-on-lenovo-t440p-nvidia-gt.html

https://gist.github.com/wangruohui/df039f0dc434d6486f5d4d098aa52d07#file-install-nvidia-driver-and-cuda-md

cuda: apt install nvidia-cuda-toolkit (then check nvcc -V)
cuDNN: https://developer.nvidia.com/rdp/cudnn-download

then update the envvar

export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=$LD_LIBRARY_PATH:/usr/local/cuda/lib64
export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=$LD_LIBRARY_PATH:/usr/lib/nvidia-384

pytorch: follow instructions from pytorch.org

tensorflow: follow instructions from https://tensorflow.org/install/install_linux
add kernel for jupyter notebook:
mkdir -p ~/.local/share/jupyter/kernels/tf
tf must contain kernel.json:
{
 "display_name": "Python 2", 
 "language": "python", 
 "argv": [
  "/home/alex/tensorflow/bin/python", 
  "-m", 
  "ipykernel_launcher", 
  "-f", 
  "{connection_file}"
 ]
}
